## Docker is the tool every company uses daily.

### What is Docker?
Imagine you build an app on your laptop, it works perfectly.
You send it to you friend's laptop "it doesn't work!"
why? Different OS, different settings, missing dependencies.
Docker solves this exact problem.

Docker = Shipping container!
real world shipping container:
-Same box work on ship, truck, train!
-contents dont' matter!
-Standard size everywhere!.

###Docker Container:
-Same app works on any computer
-Includes everything needed!.
-Run exactly the same everywhere!.

Simple Analogy:
Without Docker!
"work on my machine" problem
With Docker:
"Works EVERYWHERE" soulution!.

Image vs Container:
Docker image = Recipe
Docker Container = Actul cooked dish.

one Recipe - Can make many dishes!.
one image - Can run many containers

Real example:
Image : Ubuntu:latest
Container 1 : Running ubuntu instace
Container 2 : Another ubuntu instance
container 3 : yet another instance

All from SAME image
All independent from each other.

Docker vs VM.

VM-Heavy-slow start-full os copy-few vms per server
Docker-Light - strart in seconds-share host os- 100 of containers.

HOST OS - Ubuntu - Containers- uses HOST os Kernel
Containers are light-no separate Full os needed

HOST OS ( Ubuntu)
C1 | C2 | C3 | C4 
app  app  app  app  - Light

All share same host os kernal.

Real example with my server:
my AWS server : HOST OS = ubuntu 26.04

When you install Docker on it:
- All containers will SHARE this Ubuntu
- No need to install separate OS for each container
- super fast and lightweight

Installing Docker only ASW SERVER:
## sudo apt update - 
then
## sudo apt install docker.io -y - this install docker on server.

After installation start the docker
# sudo systemctl start docker
# sudo systemctl enable docker

verify docker is installed: 
# docker --version

## Now lets run first container !!
sudo docker run hello-world - This is the traditional Docker command evey enginners runs.
what will happen:
Docker checks if "hello-world" image exists locally.
if not, downloads from docker hub(internet)
creates a container from that image
runs it
shows a welcome message
container stops automatically

Docker Client - talked to docker daemon
Docker daemon - downloaded image from docker hub
Docker daemon - create container
container - ran and showed message
output - steamed to your terminal.

$ docker run - it ubuntu bash -
sudo docker run - it ubuntu bash

what this does:
-it - interactive terminal mode
ubuntu - download ubuntu image
bash - start bash shell inside container
